        <hl1>PORTRAIT OF A SCANDAL</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The arrest of one corrupt Los Angeles police officer has led to the biggest scandal in the history of the city's police department, and has done what even Rodney King didn't: brought the troubled department under federal supervision. A report by Lou Cannon in The Times Magazine.</p>
